      • getInitialAssigneeForPicker

        Assignee[] getInitialAssigneeForPicker()
        Helper method that returns an Assignee used to initialize an Assignee picker (used when the end user is assigning the TroubleTicket to a user/group/queue through the UI). (The return value needs to be wrapped in an array because in Pebbles a Value statement cannot write directly to a value on a page.)
        Returns:
        the Assignee the trouble ticket is currently assigned to, or if there isn't one currently assigned return the platform AutoAssignee object instead

      • getPotentialAssociatedTransactions

        IQueryBeanResult<Transaction> getPotentialAssociatedTransactions()
        Returns:
        an array containing all the transactions that can potentially be associated with this trouble ticket. Mainly used by popup chooser to list transactions from which the user can select one or more to associate explicitly with the trouble ticket

      • hasHoldWithNoTargets

        boolean hasHoldWithNoTargets()
        Determine whether this trouble ticket has holds enabled but has no related entities. If that is the case, it means holds are enabled but they are not targeting anything. We can use this method to figure out whether we should display a warning to the user about this situation
        Returns:
        true if one or more hold types are enabled for this trouble ticket, but no related entities exist for the trouble ticket

      • hasRelatedEntities

        boolean hasRelatedEntities()
        Returns:
        true if this trouble ticket has at least one related entity, false if it has none

      • isOverdue

        boolean isOverdue()
        Returns a boolean indicating whether or not the trouble ticket is overdue. Overdue means that the current date is later than the TargetDate field of the trouble ticket.
        Returns:
        true if the current date is later than the TargetDate field of the TroubleTicket, false otherwise
